<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8efd2630-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1433"><num value="1433">§ 1433.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When used in this chapter, the term—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8efd2631-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1433/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> “Secretary” means the Secretary of State.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8efd2632-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1433/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> “Department” means the Department of State.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8efd2633-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1433/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> “Government agency” means any executive department, board, bureau, commission, or other agency of the Federal Government, or independent establishment, or any corporation wholly owned (either directly or through one or more corporations) by the United States.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id8efd2634-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-01-27/ch36">Jan. 27, 1948, ch. 36</ref>, title I, § 4, <ref href="/us/stat/62/6">62 Stat. 6</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
